01:08.437 --> 01:09.737
Greetings, Professor.

01:09.805 --> 01:11.706
Oh! Somebody help!

01:13.116 --> 01:15.204
The building's empty.
No one's coming to help.

01:16.621 --> 01:17.955
Have a seat.

01:20.748 --> 01:22.782
Wh-Who are you?

01:23.152 --> 01:24.319
That...

01:24.386 --> 01:26.197
is an excellent question.

01:26.355 --> 01:28.775
But I get to ask the first one.

01:30.745 --> 01:34.262
I can fill a room or just one heart.

01:34.440 --> 01:36.659
Others may have me,
but I cannot be shared.

01:36.722 --> 01:37.917
What am I?!

01:38.628 --> 01:40.083
What?

01:40.325 --> 01:42.692
It's a riddle. Answer the riddle!

01:42.747 --> 01:45.039
Uh... I...

01:45.107 --> 01:46.107
Knowledge?

01:47.868 --> 01:50.564
Knowledge can't be shared, Professor?

01:50.650 --> 01:52.525
Really? You are the chair

01:53.103 --> 01:55.298
of a chemistry department.

01:55.376 --> 01:56.845
You've spent a career

01:56.907 --> 01:58.920
sharing knowledge!

01:58.987 --> 02:00.188
No!

02:06.595 --> 02:07.995
I apologize.

02:11.567 --> 02:13.634
I'm not myself these days.

02:17.805 --> 02:19.739
Hands, please.

02:23.764 --> 02:27.014
I can be a member of a group,
but I can never blend in.

02:27.082 --> 02:29.420
- What am I?
- I... Uh...

02:29.826 --> 02:30.918
A shadow?

02:34.238 --> 02:36.439
The answer is an individual.

02:36.625 --> 02:38.882
Duh! I expected more.

02:39.027 --> 02:40.094
But then,

02:40.886 --> 02:42.886
none of the others did very well either.

02:42.972 --> 02:45.199
- The others?
- Oh, you'd know them.

02:47.559 --> 02:48.975
One was an artist,

02:49.082 --> 02:50.585
one was a writer,

02:51.811 --> 02:53.850
one was a philosopher.

02:55.948 --> 03:01.256
The stars of Gotham's
intellectual and artistic...

03:01.482 --> 03:03.082
constellation.

03:03.160 --> 03:05.269
Fallen stars now.

03:05.671 --> 03:07.808
Wh-Why are you doing this?

03:09.366 --> 03:12.058
My best friend recently said

03:12.918 --> 03:16.816
there was no me without him.

03:19.426 --> 03:21.523
I shot him and dumped him in the river.

03:21.609 --> 03:26.156
He was a sort of guide
to me on my journey.

03:26.383 --> 03:29.771
You see, I know who I am, Professor.

03:30.473 --> 03:33.975
It's how to... be him...

03:34.691 --> 03:36.258
that is eluding me.

03:36.810 --> 03:38.686
I seek guidance.

03:39.686 --> 03:42.431
I feel your every move,
I know your every thought,

03:42.537 --> 03:46.225
I'm with you from birth,
and I'll see you when you rot.

03:46.287 --> 03:49.703
- What am I?!
- I don't know.

03:51.341 --> 03:53.109
Well, that's just too bad.

04:03.286 --> 04:05.054
No, no!

